## Core Focus Areas

### Power Independence
Backup power isn't luxury—it's necessity when storms knock out infrastructure for extended periods. We test:
- Solar generators and portable power stations
- Battery capacity vs. real-world runtime
- Solar panel charging in less-than-perfect conditions
- What actually keeps refrigerators, medical equipment, and communications running

### Water Security
Clean water becomes critical the moment municipal systems fail. Our testing covers:
- Portable filtration systems for various water sources
- Rainwater collection and storage
- Emergency purification methods
- Capacity claims vs. actual performance

### Self-Sufficient Systems
Long-term resilience requires reducing dependence on fragile supply chains:
- Food production and preservation
- Energy alternatives
- DIY systems that actually work
- Knowledge that outlasts equipment

### Reliable Gear
When equipment fails during emergencies, consequences are serious. We evaluate:
- Build quality under actual field conditions
- Performance during temperature extremes
- Longevity beyond the first few uses
- Value vs. marketing hype

