## Our Testing Standards

### Real Emergency Use
We don't simulate emergencies—we use equipment during actual power outages, storms, and infrastructure failures. Performance under stress matters more than specifications.

### Long-Term Testing
First impressions lie. We test gear over months, through multiple seasons and conditions. Equipment that works initially but fails after 60 days doesn't get recommendations.

### Honest Limitations
Perfect products don't exist. Every review includes what the product *cannot* do, what it struggles with, and who shouldn't buy it. Honest limitations build trust.

### Comparative Context
We compare products to realistic alternatives and discuss trade-offs. Understanding what you're choosing *between* matters as much as what you're choosing.

### Cost-Benefit Reality
Expensive doesn't always mean better. We evaluate actual value: does performance justify price? Are there better options at different price points?

